social_posts.post_text: New Year, Same US - 1/1/23 || Bishop, CA

I’ll spare you the senseless quotes about the ethos of travel and I’ll give it to you straight up ~ 200+ miles clocked by foot, numerous days of 2 lunches, 2 dinners with Lawsons, 7-Eleven and Family Mart stops before, in-between, and after. Around 8-12 pounds gained, 2000+ exposures taken, and a credit card statement I refuse to look at. I left no stone in my path unturned and still need 3 more visits to feel complete || Chuo City, Tokyo

1:25am- A yakitori chef takes a post-shift stroll through Omoide Yokocho aka Memory Lane; A tight alley that is comprised of 50 or so bars and restaurants linked by a pathway just wide enough for 2 people to pass. Both a local and tourist gem, the throwback alley keeps its old school charm despite being completely surrounded by the Shinjuku’s Time Square-like attractions || Shinjuku, Tokyo
Midnight in Oku-Shibu || Deep Shibuya, Tokyo

March 31st 2023- LA to Palm Springs Part 2- 19 teams- each with 7-9 runners- starting off at the Venice sign at 5am. Im always grateful for my @noshortcutstt family for bringing me on board again to document the runners as they trek 130 miles from Venice to Mid City to DTLA, East LA, San Gabriel valley, deep inland empire, Trumpland desert, to finish at the Palm Springs sign. Congrats to ALL teams who finished before midnight and special CONGRATS to one team comprised of just 2 runners who completed the race in 17 hours each running 65 miles.
The City’s motto? “Eat Until You Drop” || Osaka, Japan
Shut up and let me be a tourist || Nishiki Market, Kyoto Japan
Don’t mind me, just posting a picture of Macaque …P.S. I’m the one in the cage…P.S.S. Garcia gave up || Kyoto, Japan

Back again with my @noshortcutstt  family documenting the Los Angeles to San Diego 2023 relay race. 24 teams starting at 5am from Santa Monica zipped through the streets of Venice, Culver City, Inglewood, South Central LA onto the LA River… THEN dumped out onto the new beach route in which they toughed it all the way to the finish line in Pacific Beach, San Diego. Huge props and congrats to all runners! Special shout out to my  @ampassoc racers and to my homies(and Tuesday night training partners) 🏆 @runpdr for winning the race and finishing at 5:20pm. Finishing this race before the sun goes down is pure fucking insanity!! Extra special shout out to my baby brother @arrezeus for being my driver/navigator/assistant again!
Can’t forget about my horizontal selections from @noshortcutstt LA to SD 2023!! Thank you and sorry  again to all runners who I annoyed by yelling at them to try and hit my marks 🙌🏽😬
